# Collectives app overview

Nextcloud app for collaborative wiki-style knowledge bases backed by **Teams/Circles**.

## Stack

- **Frontend**: Vue 3, Pinia, Vue Router, `@nextcloud/vue` (NcActions, NcActionButton, NcActionLink), Vite
- **Backend**: PHP, App Framework (OCS controllers + a few web routes), custom filesystem mount
- **Editor**: Nextcloud **Text** app (`OCA.Text`) for markdown pages
- **Dependencies**: Circles/Teams, Text, Viewer

## Key directories

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/` | Vue frontend (`main.ts`, stores, components) |
| `lib/Controller/` | HTTP controllers (OCS + web) |
| `lib/Service/` | Business logic |
| `lib/Fs/`, `lib/Mount/` | Filesystem helpers and collective mount |
| `appinfo/routes.php` | All routes (Vue catch-all must stay last in `routes`) |
| `js/`, `css/` | Vite build output (committed / served to browser) |

## Page filesystem model

Pages are `.md` files on a per-collective mount:

- **Landing page**: `Readme.md` at collective root (`NodeHelper::isLandingPage`)
- **Leaf page**: `Title.md` in parent folder
- **Page with subpages**: folder `Title/` containing `Readme.md` (index page) + children (`NodeHelper::isIndexPage`)
- **Attachments**: `.attachments.{fileId}/` next to the page file
- **Templates**: `.templates/` at collective root (hidden, not exported)

Logical parent/child relationships are also tracked in DB (`PageService`, `PageInfo`).

## UI entry points for page actions

- `src/components/Page/PageActionMenu.vue` — three-dot menu (sidebar + title bar)
- `src/components/PageList/PageListItem.vue` — sidebar row; mounts `PageActionMenu` when `canEdit || isLandingPage`
- `src/components/Collective/NcActionCollectiveActions.vue` — landing-page collective actions

## Development (nextcloud-docker-dev)

- App path in container: `/var/www/html/apps-extra/collectives`
- **Node 20+** required for `npm run dev` / `npm run build`
- Collectives registers a **service worker** — stale JS is common; hard-refresh or disable SW in DevTools when testing frontend changes
- See `DEVELOPING.md` for full setup

## Conventions

- Minimize scope; match existing patterns in neighboring code
- OCS APIs live under `/api/v1.0/`; file downloads use regular web routes with `StreamResponse`
- Use `t('collectives', '...')` for user-visible strings
- Do not commit unless explicitly asked
